    'scheduler' => [
        'package'     => 'vortos/vortos-scheduler (+ vortos/vortos-scheduler-admin for the browser UI)',
        'description' => 'Distributed, multi-tenant, enterprise-grade job scheduler. Cron and interval triggers, distributed lease (SQL/Redis/Postgres Advisory) for single-execution guarantees, misfire recovery, overlap policies, RBAC+4-eyes security, HMAC hash-chain audit trail, 12 Prometheus metrics, OTel spans, circuit breaker, dead-man detector, automatic run-ledger AND fire-queue pruning with per-tenant retention overrides, and an optional HTMX+Twig admin UI. IMPORTANT: scheduler:run alone only scans/enqueues — nothing executes without also running scheduler:consume (S12 fire-queue consumer, requires vortos-cqrs). All S0–S12 blocks complete as of 2026-07.',
        'provides'    => [
            'SchedulerDaemon'           => 'Long-lived process started via scheduler:run. Tick loop: acquire lease → DueScan → MisfireResolver → SlotCalculator → FireDispatcher (atomic claim+enqueue) → sleep. Type FireDispatcherPort — accepts DispatchCircuitBreaker wrapper. Does NOT execute commands — only enqueues to vortos_scheduler_fire_queue.',
            'FireQueueConsumer'         => '(S12) Long-lived process started via scheduler:consume — required alongside SchedulerDaemon for anything to actually execute. Claims fire_queue rows (FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED on Postgres — safe for multiple replicas; single-writer only on SQLite), hydrates the payload via CommandHydrator, dispatches through Vortos\\Cqrs\\Command\\CommandBusInterface, marks the ledger row Completed/Failed. Registered only when vortos-cqrs is installed; scheduler:doctor C11 reports why if it is not.',
            'CommandHydrator'           => 'Reflection-based: hydrate(commandClass, payload): CommandInterface. Matches payload keys to the command\'s constructor named parameters. Missing required or unknown extra keys throw InvalidCommandPayloadException.',
            'ScheduleService / ScheduleServiceInterface' => 'Runtime CRUD for dynamic schedules. create/pause/resume/delete/fireNow/list/get/setRunRetentionOverride/removeRunRetentionOverride — all writes check CommandSpecValidator (allowlist) and SchedulePolicyInterface (RBAC+4-eyes) before persisting. Public service — it is the package facade; do not make it private, RemoveUnusedDefinitionsPass will prune the whole dispatch chain in a minimal container otherwise.',
            'VortosSchedulerConfig'     => 'Fluent config object (DependencyInjection/VortosSchedulerConfig.php) — same convention as VortosCacheConfig/VortosAuthConfig/etc. Loaded via config/scheduler.php + config/{env}/scheduler.php, validated through Configuration (TreeBuilder) via processConfiguration(), then consumed as a resolved array (NOT the object\'s getters — it has none) inside SchedulerExtension::load(). Replaces ~22 previously-scattered $_ENV reads.',
            '#[Scheduled]'              => 'PHP attribute on a StaticScheduleDefinition class. Discovered at compile time by StaticSchedulePass → StaticScheduleRegistry. Fields: id (UUIDv7, permanent), name (slug), cron XOR interval, command (FQCN), misfire, overlap, timezone, jitterSec, sensitive.',
            '#[SchedulableCommand]'     => 'PHP attribute on a command class. CommandSpecValidator rejects any attempt to schedule a class without this tag (CommandNotAllowlistedException). SchedulableCommandPass additionally asserts at compile time that the class implements Vortos\\Domain\\Command\\CommandInterface — a Console command class here is a deploy-time failure, not a runtime one. The allowlist prevents arbitrary code execution via the scheduler API.',
            'PruneSchedulerRunsSchedule' => 'Framework-owned #[Scheduled] static schedule — NOT app-discovered. Registered unconditionally by SchedulerExtension, gated on runRetentionDays > 0 (0 = not registered at all, no daily no-op fire). Daily 03:00 UTC + 15min jitter, OverlapPolicy::Skip, explicit SkipMissed.',
            'RunRetentionSweeper'       => 'Multi-tenant prune orchestrator, shared by the automatic path and scheduler:prune\'s default mode. Algorithm: one pruneOldRuns() call per tenant with a non-exempt override, plus one "everyone else" call at the global cutoff excluding already-handled tenants. Per-tenant override of 0 days = permanent legal hold, skipped entirely. Also invokes FireQueuePruner (optional dependency) at the end of each sweep so terminal fire-queue rows are drained on the same schedule.',
            'FireQueuePruner'           => 'Batched, time-budgeted delete of terminal (dispatched/failed) vortos_scheduler_fire_queue rows older than fireQueueRetentionDays (SCHEDULER_FIRE_QUEUE_RETENTION_DAYS, default 7; 0 disables). Pending/processing rows are never touched regardless of age (a stuck pending row is a C11 concern, not a prune candidate). Global (no per-tenant dimension) — the fire-queue is transient dispatch intent; durable history lives in runs+audit_log, hence the shorter default horizon than run retention. Same SCHEDULER_PRUNE_BATCH_SIZE / SCHEDULER_PRUNE_MAX_DURATION_SEC knobs as pruneOldRuns; cutoff format matches FireQueueConsumer\'s dispatched_at write (no UTC conversion, shared ClockPort). Registered only when fireQueueRetentionDays > 0, and only actually fires while runRetentionDays > 0 (it piggybacks the daily prune schedule). Emits vortos_scheduler_fire_queue_pruned_total.',
            'RunRetentionOverrideStoreInterface' => 'Per-tenant retention override store (tenant_id → retention_days), same trio pattern as ScheduleStatusOverrideStore (interface/DBAL driver/in-memory double/conformance TCK). Table: vortos_scheduler_run_retention_overrides.',
            'CronTrigger / IntervalTrigger' => 'CronTrigger: 5-field cron via dragonmantank/cron-expression, per-schedule timezone. IntervalTrigger: fixed N-second interval, always UTC.',
            'MisfirePolicy'             => 'SkipMissed (default), FireOnce, FireAll. Capped by SCHEDULER_MAX_CATCHUP_AGE_SECONDS (default 86400). FireAll with a long window after a long outage can produce a burst.',
            'OverlapPolicy'             => 'AllowConcurrent (default), SkipIfRunning, QueueBehind. Checked atomically inside FireDispatcher before the slot is claimed.',
            'LeasePort'                 => 'Distributed mutex port. Drivers: SqlLeaseStore (default — INSERT ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE WHERE expires_at < NOW()), RedisLeaseStore (SET NX PX), PostgresAdvisoryLeaseStore (pg_try_advisory_lock — zero-TTL, releases on disconnect), InMemoryLeaseStore. Driver key is "sql"|"redis"|"postgres-advisory"|"in-memory" (hyphenated), selected via VORTOS_SCHEDULER_LEASE_DRIVER env var + LeaseDriverPass (reads a container parameter set by SchedulerExtension from VortosSchedulerConfig, falls back to the raw env var if that parameter is absent).',
            'LeaseHeartbeatGuard'       => 'Tracks per-shard last-renewal timestamp. If renewal has been silent for >90% of SCHEDULER_LEASE_TTL_SEC, guard prevents dispatch. Catches silent DB/Redis connection failures that keep the process alive but stale.',
            'FireDispatcher'            => 'Atomic dispatch: check OverlapPolicy, INSERT run record, INSERT fire_queue entry — all in one DB transaction. Returns FireDispatchResult (Dispatched, AlreadyDispatched, OverlapSkipped, CircuitOpen).',
            'DispatchCircuitBreaker'    => 'Wraps FireDispatcherPort. Opens after SCHEDULER_CB_FAILURE_THRESHOLD consecutive failures (default 5). Returns CircuitOpen without calling inner. Probes in HalfOpen after SCHEDULER_CB_RECOVERY_WINDOW_SEC (default 30s). Returns to Closed on successful probe. Not currently exposed as its own Prometheus metric — check daemon logs for CircuitOpen results.',
            'ScheduleResolver / CachingScheduleResolver' => 'ScheduleResolver merges StaticScheduleRegistry + DbalScheduleStore + optional ScheduleStatusOverrideStore. CachingScheduleResolver adds in-process TTL cache (SCHEDULER_RESOLVER_CACHE_TTL_SEC, default 5s) for CLI/admin paths. Daemon uses raw ScheduleResolver for zero-overhead hot path.',
            'SchedulerAuditProjector'   => 'Append-only HMAC hash-chain audit log (table vortos_scheduler_audit_log). SchedulerAuditEvent cases: schedule.{created,updated,paused,resumed,deleted,approved}, fire.{dispatched,skipped_overlap,misfired,dropped}, fire.manual, leader.{acquired,lost}, runs.pruned, retention.override_{set,removed}. Chain keyed per-tenant. onRunsPruned() uses tryAppend() (never fails an already-completed prune over an audit hiccup); every other event uses append() (throws). SchedulerAuditCheckpointProjector writes periodic checkpoints (table vortos_scheduler_audit_checkpoints, created by migration 20260701000009; immutable, UNIQUE(chain_key, epoch)) so verification is O(n/epochSize) not O(n). Checkpoint rows are written only when SCHEDULER_AUDIT_HMAC_KEY is set, but the table is always migrated and is a required C5 doctor check.',
            'SchedulerAuditChainVerifier' => 'Verifies chain integrity from a known-good checkpoint. Returns SchedulerChainVerificationResult with isValid(), brokenAtEntryId, entryCount. NOT currently one of scheduler:doctor\'s C1–C11 checks — call it directly.',
            'CardinalityGuardedSchedulerMetrics' => 'Decorator over SchedulerMetricsPort. Caps distinct schedule_id label values at SCHEDULER_METRICS_MAX_CARDINALITY (default 200). Overflow fires use __overflow__ label and increment vortos_scheduler_metric_overflow_total.',
            'DeadManDetector'           => 'Per-schedule check against SCHEDULER_DEADMAN_TOLERANCE_SEC (default 300) — NOT a single daemon-wide "last tick" gauge. Raises alerts directly through Vortos\\Alerts\\AlertDispatcherInterface (requires vortos-alerts installed), not via a Prometheus metric. Not one of the C1–C11 doctor checks.',
            'SchedulerTracer'           => 'OTel spans: scheduler.fire (per dispatch), scheduler.consume (per FireQueueConsumer batch, S12), scheduler.prune (per RunRetentionSweeper sweep).',
            'SchedulerDoctor / SchedulerDoctorPort' => '11-check health suite (C1–C11): C1 cron expressions valid, C2 no name/ID collision, C3 command allowlist valid, C4 lease driver reachable, C5 migrations applied, C6 sensitive schedules have 4-eyes approval, C7 sensitive schedules have explicit misfire policy, C8 catchup bounds valid, C9 shard config valid + probe lease per shard, C10 auto-prune config+liveness (Skip if no attempt yet, Fail if >48h since last success), C11 fire-queue consumer liveness (Skip if Cqrs not installed, Fail if oldest pending row exceeds SCHEDULER_CONSUME_STALL_THRESHOLD_SEC). Exit code 0 = all pass, 1 = any fail.',
            'SchedulerPreflightCheck'   => 'Implements PreflightCheckInterface. Delegates to SchedulerDoctorPort::run(). Registered with vortos.preflight_check tag via interface_exists guard. A FAIL blocks deploy:doctor and thus any deployment.',
            'SchedulePolicy / SchedulePolicyInterface' => 'RBAC gate for all schedule operations. Default implementation integrates with Vortos auth engine. Permissions: scheduler.schedule.create/pause/resume/delete/fire_now/read, scheduler.approval.approve/reject, scheduler.retention.manage (no .own scope — admin-only, deliberately not tenant-self-service). NullSchedulePolicy allows all (internal services only).',
            'FourEyesGate'              => 'Checks SchedulePolicy::requiresFourEyesFor*() methods. On true, creates ApprovalRequest (Pending) and throws FourEyesApprovalRequiredException. Self-approval blocked (SelfApprovalException). Approve/reject via scheduler:approve CLI or admin UI.',
            'Schedule'                  => 'Immutable value object. Fields: id (ScheduleId/UUIDv7), name (slug, validated /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9_-]*$/), source (Static/Dynamic), trigger, command (CommandSpec), misfire, overlap, timezone, jitter, status (Active/Paused), tenantId, sensitive (bool), metadata (array<string,string>), version (CAS).',
            'SlotCalculator'            => 'Produces content-addressed slot key: {scheduleId}:{ISO8601_fire_time}. Slot keys are the fundamental idempotency unit — same schedule + same fire time always produce the same key. Backed by a UNIQUE(tenant_id, schedule_id, slot) DB constraint, not just application logic.',
            'NodeJitter'                => 'Lease acquisition jitter seeded from crc32(hostname:pid) — deterministic per process, avoids synchronized acquisition storms, testable without randomness.',
        ],
        'config' => [
            'VORTOS_SCHEDULER_LEASE_DRIVER'          => 'sql (default), redis, postgres-advisory, in-memory. NOTE: hyphenated "postgres-advisory", not underscored. Every key in this list is also settable via config/scheduler.php — see VortosSchedulerConfig above.',
            'VORTOS_CACHE_DSN'                       => 'Redis DSN for the redis lease driver — shares vortos-cache\'s DSN by default, not a scheduler-specific var.',
            'SCHEDULER_SHARD_COUNT'                  => 'int, default 1. Shard count — one daemon per shard, stable schedule→shard mapping via crc32(id) % count.',
            'SCHEDULER_MAX_IDLE_SEC'                 => 'int, default 60. Daemon poll interval when no shard has due work.',
            'SCHEDULER_LEASE_TTL_SEC'                => 'int, default 30. Lease TTL. Must exceed slowest expected tick.',
            'SCHEDULER_MAX_CATCHUP_AGE_SECONDS'      => 'int, default 86400. Maximum misfire lookback window.',
            'SCHEDULER_TENANT_MAX_CONCURRENT_FIRES'  => 'int, default 0 (unlimited). Per-tenant concurrent dispatch cap.',
            'SCHEDULER_ASSUMED_DONE_TTL_SECONDS'     => 'int, default 3600. How long a dispatched job is assumed "done" when no completion arrives.',
            'SCHEDULER_CB_FAILURE_THRESHOLD'         => 'int, default 5. Consecutive failures before circuit opens.',
            'SCHEDULER_CB_RECOVERY_WINDOW_SEC'       => 'int, default 30. Seconds in Open state before HalfOpen probe.',
            'SCHEDULER_RESOLVER_CACHE_TTL_SEC'       => 'int, default 5. In-process resolver cache TTL for CLI/admin paths.',
            'SCHEDULER_DEADMAN_TOLERANCE_SEC'        => 'int, default 300. Per-schedule dead-man tolerance before an alert is raised via vortos-alerts.',
            'SCHEDULER_METRICS_MAX_CARDINALITY'      => 'int, default 200. Max distinct schedule_id Prometheus label values.',
            'SCHEDULER_APPROVAL_TTL_SECONDS'         => 'int, default 86400. 4-eyes approval request TTL.',
            'SCHEDULER_AUDIT_HMAC_KEY'                => 'string, default "". Empty disables audit projection entirely (the scheduler_audit_checkpoints table is still migrated, just never written to).',
            'SCHEDULER_AUDIT_EPOCH_SIZE'              => 'int, default 1000. Entries per HMAC checkpoint epoch.',
            'SCHEDULER_RUN_RETENTION_DAYS'            => 'int, default 30. Global auto-prune retention. 0 disables auto-prune entirely (PruneSchedulerRunsSchedule not registered) — which also disables fire-queue pruning since it piggybacks the same schedule.',
            'SCHEDULER_FIRE_QUEUE_RETENTION_DAYS'     => 'int, default 7. Retention for terminal (dispatched/failed) fire-queue rows, pruned by FireQueuePruner during the daily sweep. 0 disables. Requires SCHEDULER_RUN_RETENTION_DAYS > 0 for the schedule to exist.',
            'SCHEDULER_PRUNE_BATCH_SIZE'              => 'int, default 5000. Rows deleted per chunk by the prune sweep (both runs and fire-queue).',
            'SCHEDULER_PRUNE_MAX_DURATION_SEC'        => 'int, default 240. Wall-clock budget per prune sweep; over budget → truncated=true, continues next run.',
            'SCHEDULER_CONSUME_BATCH_SIZE'            => 'int, default 50. Rows claimed per FireQueueConsumer batch.',
            'SCHEDULER_CONSUME_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC'     => 'int, default 2. Sleep between empty polls in scheduler:consume --loop.',
            'SCHEDULER_CONSUME_STALL_THRESHOLD_SEC'   => 'int, default 120. scheduler:doctor C11 threshold for "consumer looks dead".',
        ],
        'commands' => [
            'scheduler:run'               => 'Start the daemon. Long-lived process. Options: --shard=N. Exits cleanly on SIGTERM after completing the current tick. Only scans/enqueues — does NOT execute anything.',
            'scheduler:consume'           => '(S12) Start the fire-queue consumer. REQUIRED alongside scheduler:run for anything scheduled to actually execute. Options: --loop (continuous, until SIGTERM/SIGINT), --batch-size, --poll-interval. Requires vortos-cqrs installed.',
            'scheduler:list'              => 'List all schedules with status and next fire time. Options: --tenant, --status',
            'scheduler:pause'             => 'Pause a schedule by name or --id. Current run (if any) is not interrupted.',
            'scheduler:resume'            => 'Resume a paused schedule by name or --id.',
            'scheduler:run-now'           => 'Manually trigger an immediate fire outside the normal schedule. Recorded as fire.manual in audit log.',
            'scheduler:approve'           => 'Approve or reject a pending 4-eyes approval request. Args: <requestId>. Options: --action=approve|reject, --reason',
            'scheduler:prune'             => 'Prune the run ledger. Automatic by default via PruneSchedulerRunsSchedule — this is the manual escape hatch. No args: runs the same per-tenant/global policy automatically. --before=<ISO8601> [--tenant=<id>]: explicit cutoff, bypasses policy entirely, audited with resolved=false. Options also: --actor, --dry-run, --json.',
            'scheduler:retention:set'     => 'Set (or replace) a tenant\'s run-retention override. --days=0 is a permanent legal-hold exemption, distinct from the global 0 (which disables auto-prune entirely). Requires scheduler.retention.manage. Options: --tenant, --days, --actor, --reason.',
            'scheduler:retention:remove'  => 'Remove a tenant\'s run-retention override, reverting to the global default. Requires scheduler.retention.manage. Options: --tenant, --actor.',
            'scheduler:doctor'            => 'Run 11-check health suite (C1–C11). Exit 0 = all pass, 1 = any fail.',
        ],
    ],

    'iac' => [
        'package'     => 'vortos/vortos-iac',
        'description' => 'Export real infrastructure to deterministic Terraform JSON (Kafka topics, object-store buckets, compute, database, network, queue, cache, DNS, IAM — 10 exporter families), then plan/apply/destroy through a policy-gated, audited, blast-radius-limited lifecycle. Terraform stays the provisioning engine; this is codegen + governance around it, not a replacement.',
        'provides'    => [
            '#[InfraConfig]'               => 'Marks a Terraform export configuration class. Deployment concern — canonical home is src/Shared/Infrastructure/Iac/, NOT per bounded context. Resource shape (partitions, retention) stays in MessagingConfig; InfraConfig only chooses providers and output files.',
            '#[RegisterTerraformExporter]' => 'Method attribute returning an exporter definition, e.g. KafkaTopicsExporterDefinition::create(\'kafka-topics\')->provider(KafkaProvider::Confluent)->clusterRef(\'confluent_kafka_cluster.main\')->outputFile(\'infra/kafka_topics.tf.json\'). Compiled to a static spec at container build time.',
            'Env → Terraform variables'    => 'Env references in definitions export as typed Terraform variables (sensitive when the name looks secret) — values NEVER appear in generated files; operators supply them via terraform.tfvars. SASL/SSL/DSN are never exported.',
            'TerraformDocument secret gate' => 'Lives in the renderer itself, not per-exporter, so no exporter can bypass it: a literal string assigned to a secret-looking attribute name fails the export unless explicitly allow-listed. Output renders deterministically (sorted keys, stable formatting) — same input always produces byte-identical .tf.json, which is what makes --check an exact CI gate.',
            'IacLifecycleService::apply()' => 'Three guards before anything touches infrastructure: guardPlanFile() re-hashes the plan file (PlanStaleException if it changed since plan), guardBlastRadius() refuses more than maxDestructiveProd (default 0!) destructive changes in prod without an explicit override, guardPolicy() runs your PlanPolicyInterface rules.',
            'PlanPolicyInterface'          => 'Your own org-specific rules (region restrictions, required tags, etc.) — an Ops Kit driver port, evaluated against every plan before apply.',
            'IacDriftAuditor'              => 'Detects when real infrastructure has drifted from what\'s declared. Feeds Deploy\'s doctor check (IacDriftCheck) — a deploy fails preflight against drifted infra rather than deploying onto it blind.',
        ],
        'config'      => null,
        'commands'    => [
            'vortos:iac:export'        => 'Generate all configured Terraform files. Flags: --check (CI drift guard, exit 1 on mismatch), --dry-run (print to stdout)',
            'vortos:iac:plan'          => 'Plan against a target environment. Flags: --env',
            'vortos:iac:apply'         => 'Apply a previously generated plan (requires the exact, unmodified plan file — see guardPlanFile). Flags: --env',
            'vortos:iac:destroy'       => 'Destroy environment infrastructure. Flags: --env',
